<h1 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-Overview"><strong>Overview</strong></h1>
<p>The purpose of this document is to compile the developer standards used =
throughout the development of OAS/OAC projects. These standards are designe=
d to be a starting point and guideline for good development standards, this=
 is not an exhaustive list.</p>
<h1 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-General">General</h1>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"full-width" data-local-id=
=3D"c79c6278-ad59-4e9a-80a5-44fe2e36f9e8" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 48.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 1152.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 600.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>#</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Recommendation</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Justification</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>1</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No Errors should be introduced during development</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Errors can result in failure in report execution or unexpected query gen=
eration</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>2</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No Warnings should be introduced during development, with the exception =
of expected warnings e.g. Changes to Database Features</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Warnings can result in unexpected query generation</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-RPD">RPD</h1>
<h2 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-PhysicalLayer">Physical Layer</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"full-width" data-local-id=
=3D"1677a0ff-4ef7-4283-9ac4-f6b0efcbf2dc" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 48.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 1152.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 600.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>#</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Recommendation</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Justification</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>1</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Create Aliases for all physical tables. These should all follow a naming=
 standard e.g. "Dim_", "Fact_" or "Fact_Agg_"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Aliases enable the use of =E2=80=9Croleplay=E2=80=9D tables (e.g. the Ca=
lendar dimension). It also assists with the readability of the RPD and help=
s when building development accelerators</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>2</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When possible, configure your connection pools to use a "native driver" =
to connect to your physical databases. For example, use OCI for connecting =
to an Oracle database rather than ODBC</p>
<p></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This will help with query performance when using a native driver as oppo=
sed to ODBC</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>3</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A seperate connection pool should be set up for variables and queries</p=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Variables can =E2=80=9Chog=E2=80=9D connections and cause problems when =
users are signing in to OAS/OAC.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-BusinessModelLayer(BM)">Business Model Lay=
er (BM)</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"full-width" data-local-id=
=3D"abd99698-89ab-45fb-974b-efff52963ef6" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 48.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 1152.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 600.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>#</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Recommendation</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Justification</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>1</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All Logical Tables should be prefixed with either "Dim =E2=80=93 ", "Fac=
t =E2=80=93 " or "Fact&nbsp;Att =E2=80=93"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Assists with the readability of the RPD and helps when building developm=
ent accelerators</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>2</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Non-business orientated columns should be introduced into the BM</p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>End users should not be exposes to database-related objects.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>3</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Physical Primary Keys or Surrogate Keys, i.e. _sk &amp; _dk, &nbsp;shoul=
d not be present on the Business Model layer (unless, for example, you have=
 a Primary Key such as Order Id which will be displayed on reports)</p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>End users should not be exposes to database-related objects.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>4</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Dimension Logical Tables must always have a Logical Key assigned. The Lo=
gical Key should be something "business oriented" such as "Employee Login" =
rather than "EMPLOYEE_PK"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>5</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Dimension Logical Tables must only contain dimension attributes, they sh=
ould never contain any measure columns (which have an Aggregate Rule)</p></=
td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This will cause a warning/error in the Admin Tool. All aggregation shoul=
d be done on logical facts.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>6</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Fact Logical Tables should never have a Logical Key assigned</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>7</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Every Logical Column within a Fact Logical Table must be a measure colum=
n, and therefore have an Aggregation Rule assigned. Non-aggregatable fact v=
alues should be held in a logical dimension based on the fact table</p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>8</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The Business Model should only consist of logical star-schemas, there sh=
ould not be any snow-flaking</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>9</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Every Dimension Logical Table should have a corresponding Dimension Hier=
archy (with "Total" as a Grand Total level, and "Detail" at the lowest leve=
l)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This is to assist the bi server when selecting the most optimal LTS to u=
se for a given query.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>10</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Each level of a Dimension Hierarchy should have its "Number of Elements"=
 appropriately set (there is a utility that can do this automatically for y=
ou</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This is to assist the bi server when selecting the most optimal LTS to u=
se for a given query.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>11</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Every Logical Table Source within every dimension and fact Logical Table=
 should have its "Content Levels" appropriately set</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This is to assist the bi server when selecting the most optimal LTS to u=
se for a given query.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>12</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Logical Table Sources should retain the name of the source alias where p=
ossible</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This is to assist with readbility of the RPD and to help trace potential=
 issues in user reports</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>13</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>For your Dimension Hierarchies, only enable the "Ragged" and "Skip Level=
" options if your hierarchies genuinely contain Ragged and/or Skip Levels</=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>These options cause the bi server to generate far more complex SQL than =
may be necessary. Only use these options when they are necessary.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-PresentationLayer">Presentation&nbsp;Layer=
</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"full-width" data-local-id=
=3D"f3f719df-444b-4d10-beb1-4be3264326c2" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 48.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 1152.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 600.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>#</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Recommendation</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Justification</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>1</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When you have multiple Subject Areas, list the common dimensions in the =
same order across all the Subject Areas</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This is to help end users understand that these are the same logical =E2=
=80=9Cthing=E2=80=9D</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>2</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Ensure sub folders are nested within a parent/child hierarchy structure<=
/p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This is to help with the navigate and usability of a subject area</p></t=
d>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>3</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Presentation Table names within each Subject Area must not begin with "D=
im =E2=80=93 " or "Fact =E2=80=93" or "Fact Compound =E2=80=93". So remove =
these prefixes if they are present after creating the Subject Area by dragg=
ing Logical Tables directly from the Business Model</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>End users should not be exposes to database-related objects.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>4</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The Presentation Table containing facts should be listed right at the bo=
ttom, and the Presentation Table should be called "Measures"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This is to help with the navigate and usability of a subject area</p></t=
d>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>5</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Every Subject Area should have a corresponding role defined in the RPD&n=
bsp;=E2=86=92 (Tools =E2=86=92 Identity) and access to that SA should <stro=
ng>only</strong> be via that role (SA access is then handled by role mappin=
g &amp; hierarchy within EM). This way a 'deny-by-default' approach is achi=
eved.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>6</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Any secured columns (e.g access control) will show the padlock icon to d=
emonstrate that a security rule is in place</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p></p>
<h1 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-PresentationCatalog"><strong>Presentation =
Catalog</strong></h1>
<h2 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-Reports">Reports</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"full-width" data-local-id=
=3D"1a40addc-1382-4075-8e9f-3ff7702d11c2" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 48.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 1152.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 600.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>#</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Recommendation</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Justification</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>1</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The names of objects in the catalogue should be unique across the whole =
webcat instance</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>This makes a given object easier to find.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>2</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Object names should be concise and in the majority of cases be used as t=
he display title within each report (Default option). Use the following nam=
ing conventions (minus the single quotation mark)&nbsp;to automatically gro=
up together similar items within a sorted folder:-</p>
<p><strong>PROMPT</strong> names should begin with 'Prompt_'</p>
<p><strong>PRESENTATION VARIABLES</strong> should begin with 'PV_'</p>
<p><strong>FILTER</strong> names should be with 'Filter_'</p>
<p><strong>FOLDER&nbsp;NAMES</strong>&nbsp;should be relevant to the projec=
t and aligned with Security Access, typically by Department / User Function=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>3</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Ensure that all users have their local settings set to English - United =
Kingdom (where applicable!) and if using Internet Explorer ensure Enterpris=
e Mode is toggled off</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>4</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Always populate the default 'No Results View' by editing the properties =
of the default compound view to include the following:-</p>
<p>The Header should contain the title of the report.</p>
<p>The Text box should contain:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">&lt;b&gt=
;*** No data was returned for the selections you made. ***&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;style
type=3D=E2=80=9Dtext/css=E2=80=9D&gt;
td.ResultLinksCell {
display:none;
}
&lt;/style&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>5</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Limit the size of dashboard reports to a consistent size to ensure they =
fit into dashboards, currently: 400 x 275. The chart zooming feature can be=
 used if required but should be avoided since the aim of the dashboards is =
to present results =E2=80=98at a glance=E2=80=99 without having to perform =
extensive navigation.&nbsp; NO HORIZONTAL SCROLLING.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>6</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Use conditional formatting to highlight extreme/out of normal range valu=
es. when applicable</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>7</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Unless inappropriate or otherwise specified, allow the standard drill-do=
wn features. In dashboard sections switch on Drill-in-place</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>8</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Switch drill off when no drilling is required</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>9</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When building reports always begin your design by filtering the data to =
ensure you do not affect server performance, especially in the production s=
ystem. Typically restrict the data to one week=E2=80=99s-worth initially, t=
hen once you have your layout where you want it increase the time period</p=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>10</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Report Prompts have improved over the 10g version, but are still not ide=
al. This is because once the selection has been made in a Report Prompt, th=
e prompt and its values disappear and are replaced by the report. Where pos=
sible use Dashboard Prompts instead of Report Prompts</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>11</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Use presentation variables in preference to =E2=80=98Is Prompted=E2=80=
=99 to apply dashboard prompts. This is because =E2=80=98Is Prompted=E2=80=
=99 will only apply correctly if the table_name.column_name in the dashboar=
d prompt match those in report. In many cases we are prompting for a date f=
rom one table but using it across different date tables within the reports =
across the dashboard page</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>12</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>When using presentation variables in filters always include a default va=
lue. This ensures that when developing the reports and running them outside=
 of a dashboard, that they do not affect server performance. The defaults w=
ill be overwritten with the dashboard prompt defaults once the report is pl=
aced on a dashboard. The same defaults need to be applied if the presentati=
on variables are used in column logic. To ensure the correct data type of d=
ate presentation variables use the additional type syntax: @{pv_date}{date =
=E2=80=982011-03-30=E2=80=99}. Note that the format of the date here must b=
e YYYY-MM-DD</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>13</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Apply saved filters instead of expanding filter content within reports f=
or ease of maintenance should the filter subsequently change</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-Dashboards">Dashboards</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"full-width" data-local-id=
=3D"2b0c8b6f-10eb-4f78-a3d9-e992bb326228" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 48.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 1152.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 600.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>#</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Recommendation</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Justification</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>1</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The number of different dashboard prompts should be kept down to an abso=
lute minimum. Each prompt should also contain the minimum number of element=
s</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>2</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Try to ensure that where possible the columns across the prompts are in =
the same order</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>3</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Use the =E2=80=98Limit By=E2=80=99 feature where two or more elements on=
 the prompt are related</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>4</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Prompts should include a default values where possible to ensure that th=
e reports on the page bring back the minimum amount of data when first open=
ed</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>5</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The =E2=80=98All Choices=E2=80=99, option should be used where possible<=
/p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>6</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All prompts should have a scope of =E2=80=98Dashboard=E2=80=99 unless th=
ere is a very good reason against. Users will be expecting their selected p=
rompt values to persist across the pages of their dashboard</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"OADevelopmentStandards-Style">Style</h2>
